<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#800000">Originally posted by Jelen of Brell on 10-10-2000 07:36 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">About the stats - very true, do NOT listen to the books.

About picking a melee class.. Obviously this person has not played a casting class.

My first character was a Mage, my second a Shaman.  I play 8 characters now, intermixed Meleer's, Casters, priests and hybrids.

First off, rogues are NOT easy.  Probably one of the hardest classes to solo, and to learn to play a rogue correctly - i.e. using your Evade skills, positioning for backstabs, Instilling Doubt etc.. is just as hard as playing any caster.  In fact, most casters have certain advantages in battle, and have a much EASIER time soloing things if played correctly.

Pick a class you ENJOY, not one thats's necessarily "easy" .. 

Some key points.

Pure casters (Mages/Ench/Necros/Wiz) put all your bonus points in Intelligence (at least most)

Priests (Clerics, Druids, Shamans) put all points in Wisdom (at least most)

Melee classes are harder to assign stats, must use your judgement based on what your class needs most, and what stats your race already excels in.  I think STR and DEX are important factors nonetheless.

Bards and Enchanters should have high charisma for charming/mezzing.

STR - how hard you hit, how often you hit, how much you can carry.
DEX - proc's are effected by this, combat is slightly affected, channeling skill increase is affected by this
STA - resistance to stuns, holding your breath, long runs, how many times you can swing that big heavy axe.
AGI - affects AC, I think it helps with dodge and parry
WIS - Priest type stat, affects your mana supply 
INT - Pure caster type stat, affects your mana supply
CHA - affects how much vendors buy/sell things to you, and success of mezmerizing, charm spells

NOTE: The highest of your WIS or INT is known to affect how well you perform your trade skills (successes vs. failures)

Treat people right!

Just my two cents.

Jelen Melenkurion
Mystical Avengers
Level 40 Shaman (among many others)
Brell Serilis Server</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
